  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age range 14-70 years old

          -  Histological confirmed, previously untreated stage I/II NK/T cell lymphoma in the
             upper-aerodigestive tract

          -  ECOG performance status 0-1

          -  Life expectancy of more than 3 months

          -  Without prior history of pancreatitis

          -  Adequate bone marrow and organ functions

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Low risk population (Definition: stage I without local invasion, B symptoms and high
             LDH level)

          -  Pregnant or lactating women

          -  With contraindication of steroid including uncontrolled diabetes

          -  Serious uncontrolled diseases and intercurrent infection

          -  History of other malignancies except cured basal cell carcinoma of skin and carcinoma
             in-situ of uterine cervix
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
